Variation. Male length: 10–13 mm , width 3–5 mm . Female length: 8–12 , width 3–5 mm . Paratypes similar to holotype and allotype except the following characters: males with less developed mandibles (
Figs. 12– 14
) with less developed process and outer margin regularly convex, pronotum strongly punctured and less elevated, some females with protibial teeth less developed.
